Embattled NPA head Shaun Abrahams is appearing before Parliament&#8217;s Justice Portfolio Committee over his decision to charge Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan. Embattled National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) head Shaun Abrahams faces a grilling today when he appears before Parliament s Justice Portfolio Committee.He s been summoned to explain to Members of Parliament the circumstances surrounding his initial decision to charge Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan and former South African Revenue Services (Sars) executives, Ivan Pillay and Oupa Magashula and his subsequent about-turn.